    "recap_headline": "California Baptist University",
    "recap_text": "RIVERSIDE---\nThe bats were hot on Friday night as California Baptist baseball welcomed the University of Evansville to Totman Stadium for the first game of a three-set series. CBU secured the 11-6 win with eight hits and staved off multiple attempts by the Purple Aces to come back. The Lancers improve to 18-5 on the season and will go for their sixth series win tomorrow evening.\nDespite dropping an early lead, the Lancers settled in and slowly began racking up their hits, beginning with a two-RBI home run by\nBen Castelli\n. The Aces punched right back in the top of the second with two runs of their own to trade the lead again, but a\nCarter Eberhard\nhomer would bring home two runs before\nRyder Dykstra\nknocked an RBI single for a 4-3 lead. From there, the Lancers slowly began building on their runs as the bottom of the sixth drove in three runs courtesy of CBU capitalizing on the Aces' errors.\nFor the first time this season,\nMichael Malki\nstruggled on the mound, and\nGary Adcock\nlooked to his relievers for help, creating a bullpen game on Friday night.\nCameron Teper\nwas solid through 4.1 innings and delivered six strikeouts while allowing just one run before\nLuis Becerra\n,\nSam Burgess\n, and\nZachary Yates\ndid their job to finish out the win. The victory over Evansville comes as Teper's fourth pitching win and Yates' second save for the Lancers.\nThe Lancers will be back at Totman Stadium tomorrow evening for the second installment of the weekend series at 5 p.m.",
